window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Torian Ranth has protected the university from the Viper. Now he must use him.</b></p> <p>There are none at the university who can teach Torian what it means for him to be a valsahir. When the headmaster suggests he convince the Viper to teach him, Torian must first prove he’s worthy.</p> <p>As secrets begin to unravel, the distinction between friend and foe blurs. The Viper, once thought an adversary, becomes an enigma, compelling Torian to grapple with a dangerous dilemma. Is the Viper genuinely the sinister force they have all feared?</p> <p>But a tangible threat forces him to make a choice. Rusav, relentless in their quest for destruction, look to liberate the Viper, their linchpin to obliterating Navarin.</p> <p>Torian must find his own truths to protect those embroiled in a war that should never have been theirs to fight—even if it means defying everything he’s come to believe.</p> <p><b>Book 3 in a new Progression Fantasy series from bestseller D.K. Holmberg. This is coming-of-age magic academy fantasy with a weak-to-strong progression into power, perfect for fans of </b><b><i>Mark of the Fool</i></b><b>, </b><b><i>Cradle</i></b><b>, and </b><b><i>Bastion</i></b><b>.</b></p>"; 
